@startuml admin-layout-structure
!theme plain
title Admin Application - Layout Structure

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

component "App.vue" as App

package "Router (/admin)" {
    [Login View] as Login
    [Forbidden View] as Forbidden

    package "Admin Layout" {
        [AdminLayout] as Layout

        package "Topbar" {
            [AdminTopbar] as TopbarComp
        }

        package "Sidebar" {
            [AdminSidebar] as SidebarComp
        }

        [router-view] as RouterView
    }
}

App --> Login : /admin/login
App --> Forbidden : /admin/forbidden
App --> Layout : /admin/* (protected)

Layout --> TopbarComp
Layout --> SidebarComp
Layout --> RouterView

package "Admin Views" {
    [Dashboard] as Dashboard
    [UserList] as UserList
    [UserDetails] as UserDetails
    [PlanList] as PlanList
    [AnalyticsDashboard] as Analytics
}

RouterView --> Dashboard : /admin/
RouterView --> UserList : /admin/users
RouterView --> UserDetails : /admin/users/:id
RouterView --> PlanList : /admin/plans
RouterView --> Analytics : /admin/analytics

note right of Layout
  **AdminLayout Structure**

  ┌────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Topbar                         │
  ├────────┬───────────────────────┤
  │        │                       │
  │ Side-  │  Main Content         │
  │ bar    │  ~<router-view />     │
  │        │                       │
  │        │                       │
  └────────┴───────────────────────┘
end note

note bottom of SidebarComp
  Navigation items dynamically
  highlight based on current route.

  Each item links to plugin routes:
  - Dashboard → /admin/
  - Users → /admin/users
  - Plans → /admin/plans
  etc.
end note

note left of TopbarComp
